Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.17,1:27:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Peter Lind.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.17,1:27:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Lin.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.17,1:27:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do Peter Lind.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.83,1:27:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to do Peter Lind's theory.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.83,1:27:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Not Peter Lind personally.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.83,1:27:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,His theory.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.83,1:27:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates over 480, 485, 480, that's a very, very high level intellectual acuity, 480.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.47,1:27:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we would guess that at 480, he's quite likely correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.36,1:27:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So, these are the history of mankind, the intellectual history of mankind,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.86,1:27:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,beginning really with Plato, beginning around 350 BC in Greece,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:37.56,1:27:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the golden period of Greece, has frankly not been improved on in the centuries since.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.44,1:27:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, guys, I don't mean to say that, I don't mean that personally,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:48.84,1:27:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,but frankly, not much has been discovered since Socrates or Plato in the intellectual realm.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.99,1:28:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see, intellectual integrity, and we always point out Engels just on the border of 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.09,1:28:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's the cause of a couple hundred million people's death, Karl Marx at 130.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.51,1:28:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the calibration is very important, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.64,1:28:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of one person, you have Einstein.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:14.76,1:28:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of a hundred, you have Einstein.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.28,1:28:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of a hundred, you have Einstein.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.62,1:28:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You have Socrates.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.12,1:28:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And out of 130, you've got enormous destruction.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:23.14,1:28:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The gulags, Stalin put to death tens of millions.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.86,1:28:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Chairman Mao's 30 million people starved.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.30,1:28:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see, it's not just academic.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.40,1:28:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This 130 has caused the life of probably 300 million people, probably half a billion,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.82,1:28:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's not done yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:42.54,1:28:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The killing fields.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.23,1:28:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.23,1:28:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,How important that is, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.32,1:28:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And Darwin at 450.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.55,1:28:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Darwinism is at 450.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:52.64,1:28:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, intelligent design.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.38,1:28:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I always forget what intelligent design is that.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.95,1:29:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we do intelligent design?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:01.95,1:29:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to do intelligent design.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.94,1:29:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over 450, 460, 455, 450.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.13,1:29:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's right at 450.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.48,1:29:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.48,1:29:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Intelligent design at 450.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:16.48,1:29:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.83,1:29:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought it would be a little higher than that.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.43,1:29:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Well the intelligence is innate biologically.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:24.45,1:29:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.45,1:29:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, people don't like it because it's a slippery slope.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.45,1:29:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Next thing you're going to say is behind intelligent design, there's a divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:31.45,1:29:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's the slippery slope argument.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:35.45,1:29:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.45,1:29:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So we could, of course, spend, you know, several lectures just on the content of all of this.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.74,1:29:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,These were my companions of childhood.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:44.74,1:29:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, everybody was out there playing stickball.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.74,1:29:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I was stuck in a chair because we had the great books of the western world.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.74,1:29:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,great books of the Western world and I so I was a you know the little ectomorph
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.14,1:30:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,with glasses well other guys are doing disgusting things like digging their
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.72,1:30:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,fingers in each other's eyes and mud and socking each other and jumping each
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.04,1:30:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,other I was reading Socrates okay so okay there we go the next here we have
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.29,1:30:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,we talked about context proximate content and the event this is the basis
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.34,1:30:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of course situation of ethics then an event cannot be understood comprehended
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.96,1:30:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,or judged unless you state the context and this is the avenue for political
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.82,1:30:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,fallacy you know people attack a certain concept and then they for온 then but
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.35,1:30:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't state the context they don't state the context
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.43,1:30:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.61,1:30:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,which totally changes it.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:48.23,1:30:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So one way of rhetorical falsehood
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.85,1:30:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is to purposely omit the context.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.64,1:30:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Is a certain thing okay or not okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.58,1:31:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Depends on a lot of things, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.24,1:31:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Like whether you're at war or not,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:03.02,1:31:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,makes the next letter.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.76,1:31:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you're poor or not,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.16,1:31:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,whether you're getting insurance money.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.68,1:31:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, a lot of it all depends on context.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:11.36,1:31:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, of course, courts recognize that.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.90,1:31:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called motivation.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.20,1:31:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So how severe should the punishment be?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.96,1:31:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it depends on the context.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.16,1:31:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Then sometimes that's misused
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.64,1:31:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,because the person is mentally ill,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.58,1:31:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no consequences.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.84,1:31:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should mentally ill people
Dialogue: 0,1:31:30.06,1:31:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,be exempt from consequences
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.56,1:31:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,when mentally healthy people pay them?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.42,1:31:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me why they should be excused.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:37.46,1:31:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they should be handled differently,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:39.50,1:31:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and I agree with that.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.96,1:31:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So sometimes this contextualization
Dialogue: 0,1:31:42.96,1:31:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,is misused by certain judges,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.66,1:31:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,as we see on the evening news.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.70,1:31:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, next.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:49.88,1:31:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Content field.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.16,1:31:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the content is linear.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:53.95,1:31:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the time and space,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.19,1:31:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the Newtonian dimension of causality.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.15,1:32:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Causality is based on force over time,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:02.95,1:32:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and it has to do with location.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.43,1:32:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, how it links in with Peter Lynch's
Dialogue: 0,1:32:08.91,1:32:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,recent discovery is quite interesting.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.94,1:32:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The approximate field,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.24,1:32:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,we talk about the spiritual ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:18.54,1:32:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And teachers should always be sure
Dialogue: 0,1:32:21.78,1:32:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to bring this up, the spiritual ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.00,1:32:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And I feel that a teacher's responsible
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.56,1:32:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to make sure that you hear about the downside
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.66,1:32:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,before you fall into it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.24,1:32:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The more you learn,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.64,1:32:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the more the spiritual,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.68,1:32:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego is threatened.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:36.42,1:32:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's clever.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.88,1:32:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It camouflages itself
Dialogue: 0,1:32:40.14,1:32:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and comes back as spiritual ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.52,1:32:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That you're more holy than somebody else
Dialogue: 0,1:32:44.58,1:32:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and this and that.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.56,1:32:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And spiritual teachers get it too.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.94,1:32:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual teachers get it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:51.62,1:32:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You can tell by the grandiosity
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.24,1:32:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of the robes and the giant palaces
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.60,1:32:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and the retinue and the drama
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.60,1:33:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and the theatrics that go with the whole presentation.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.82,1:33:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So the spiritual ego
Dialogue: 0,1:33:03.28,1:33:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,takes the place of the old ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.23,1:33:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, as you let the spiritual ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.87,1:33:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,you do the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.99,1:33:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The spiritual ego's getting some kind of juice over this.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.67,1:33:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.01,1:33:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Feeling more holy, that means you're superior.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.99,1:33:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That's pride.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.43,1:33:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's very easy to see the spiritual ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:22.87,1:33:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,If somebody warns you,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.90,1:33:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,it's inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.92,1:33:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,As you advance, the spiritual ego's going to come up.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.26,1:33:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.22,1:33:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Because frankly, in some ways,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:31.64,1:33:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you are holier than a lot of people.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.90,1:33:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, nobody here's going to blow up
Dialogue: 0,1:33:37.52,1:33:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,a busload of innocent children, are you?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:40.12,1:33:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody here want to blow up a busload of kids?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.40,1:33:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Meet me later.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.36,1:33:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll meet you later, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:47.22,1:33:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,To prove how holier you are,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:49.00,1:33:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll blow up a busload of kids.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:50.56,1:33:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You put dynamite around yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.98,1:33:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and you blow yourself up, all right?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:54.51,1:33:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:54.99,1:33:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So our spiritual ego says,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.37,1:33:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,God, how stupid.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:58.53,1:33:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.73,1:34:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,it calibrates at 90.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:01.37,1:34:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you sell people on something
Dialogue: 0,1:34:03.41,1:34:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that calibrates at 90, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.70,1:34:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So the spiritual ego comes up
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.26,1:34:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and we have to watch it.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.38,1:34:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we attack this ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.12,1:34:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This one's easy to see right off the chart.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.54,1:34:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This one we got to watch
Dialogue: 0,1:34:16.90,1:34:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,because it sneaks up.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:18.66,1:34:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's called holier than thou.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.78,1:34:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That's also the far-left position,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:24.84,1:34:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the far-left political position.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:25.96,1:34:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's holier than thou.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.18,1:34:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called spiritual superiority
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.32,1:34:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,or whatever they call it.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.58,1:34:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They call it spiritually correct, correct, correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.13,1:34:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.75,1:34:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see the ego appeal to be correct
Dialogue: 0,1:34:36.41,1:34:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,because if you're correct,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.77,1:34:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,then everybody else is incorrect.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.77,1:34:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a neat place to be, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.27,1:34:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.09,1:34:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual, I mean, what do they call it?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.83,1:34:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Politically correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:46.69,1:34:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,PC or...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:46.95,1:34:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.07,1:34:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:51.45,1:34:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.73,1:34:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you sound idealistic,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.07,1:34:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,which you don't realize you're feeling.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.65,1:34:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You're sounding adolescent.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:57.13,1:34:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You're sounding adolescent.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.62,1:35:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But you think you're superior.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.06,1:35:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so that's the spiritual ego coming up.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:03.82,1:35:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And it loves to feed on being superior and correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.80,1:35:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, superior.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:07.60,1:35:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:07.92,1:35:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Seriously.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.20,1:35:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Politically superior, correct, whatever it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:11.76,1:35:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we'll move on then.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.94,1:35:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The virtues are often overlooked.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.80,1:35:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,These, we presume,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:21.58,1:35:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,are part and parcel of traditional bringing up in America.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.12,1:35:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The America I grew up,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:28.60,1:35:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,which is now ridiculed as traditional America,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.90,1:35:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,this was reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:34.22,1:35:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And everybody was pretty much this way, frankly.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.18,1:35:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody was pretty much in the positive 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:42.26,1:35:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They certainly were in the 300s.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:44.61,1:35:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If you were moving, all your neighbors offered to help.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:47.51,1:35:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,They offered to loan you a van, a truck,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.72,1:35:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and moved into a new neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.16,1:35:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole neighborhood was in the positive 200s.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.28,1:35:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All the ladies around brought in a cake that they'd baked,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.62,1:35:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and they greeted you and told you who they were.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.96,1:35:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If you lent somebody your lawnmower,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:59.46,1:36:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you always got it back.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:01.44,1:36:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I guess compared to nowadays,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:05.84,1:36:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,it was a dream world.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.94,1:36:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,A dream world.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:09.97,1:36:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, a really good neighbor
Dialogue: 0,1:36:11.63,1:36:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,not only returns it, but sharpens the blade
Dialogue: 0,1:36:13.83,1:36:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,so it comes back in better shape than it was.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.75,1:36:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So all of us strove to be that kind of thoughtful,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.35,1:36:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,considerate, easygoing,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:23.05,1:36:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,non-malicious, non-salacious,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:26.35,1:36:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and pornography was not cool or in.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:30.75,1:36:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was a reasonably virtuous foundation.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.19,1:36:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And I say, before you go on to become enlightened this week,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:38.83,1:36:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,just look down and ask, in what ways here can I be warmer to people,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:43.21,1:36:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,more kind?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:44.41,1:36:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And you'll see, no matter how far you are along the spiritual pathway,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:49.12,1:36:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,these are always open.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:50.72,1:36:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You can always be a little more tolerant.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.60,1:36:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You can always...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.98,1:36:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You can always reject being upset by something that goes on
Dialogue: 0,1:36:57.20,1:37:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and say, I'm choosing to remain calm the heck with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:02.47,1:37:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You can always be more respectful, perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:07.97,1:37:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Be more sane.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:09.19,1:37:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if that's possible, but we try.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.13,1:37:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's a little messy,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:14.43,1:37:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and messy can be a little more original.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:16.65,1:37:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So we try to be friendly and cordial.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:19.05,1:37:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We try to be a good host to everyone we run into.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:23.31,1:37:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you do that,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:24.25,1:37:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll achieve what I call good personhood.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:29.00,1:37:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And you may say, well, I presume that's the way everybody is.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.56,1:37:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:33.52,1:37:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Because as you thank clerks and various people like that,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:37.70,1:37:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll often see their face go up.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.61,1:37:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people, you give them the credit card, and you walk away.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:45.65,1:37:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody says, gee, thanks for the trouble.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:47.59,1:37:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just, wow, I mean, it sort of knocks them over.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:50.77,1:37:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Just being kind to people,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:53.34,1:37:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's loving to be appreciated,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:56.72,1:37:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to give recognition.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:58.52,1:38:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So one way you can be loving to people
Dialogue: 0,1:38:00.28,1:38:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is to give recognition to who they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:02.84,1:38:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.47,1:38:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The guy who picks up our trash,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:06.39,1:38:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the big monster truck,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.21,1:38:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,always falls over when we tell him,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:09.95,1:38:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,gee, you're doing a great job.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:11.41,1:38:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, I give him five or ten bucks anyway,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:13.15,1:38:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,just because it's more than just saying it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:16.21,1:38:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You actually do mean it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.07,1:38:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And he always goes,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:18.73,1:38:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, nobody complimented him
Dialogue: 0,1:38:21.81,1:38:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,for bringing up their trash.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:24.51,1:38:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:24.99,1:38:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,just try,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:26.33,1:38:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,try for fun,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:27.11,1:38:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and you'll see the amazing response of people.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:29.77,1:38:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll think, well, everybody says thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:31.45,1:38:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,No, they do not.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.12,1:38:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If I ask the trash man,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:34.44,1:38:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,how many people run up,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.46,1:38:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and as you dump them,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:36.54,1:38:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,gee, say thanks,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:37.60,1:38:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,thanks a lot.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:38.72,1:38:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll tell you nobody, frankly.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:41.92,1:38:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's always room for,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:44.14,1:38:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,always room for improvement.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:47.80,1:38:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter where you are,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:49.50,1:38:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,there's still room for improvement.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.38,1:38:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Still room for improvement.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:53.02,1:38:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially with one's spouse.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:56.46,1:38:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a great area for improvement.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.59,1:39:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the two of you always bring up what needs to be looked at.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:05.61,1:39:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why it's so valuable.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:07.27,1:39:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see you're being, you know, short-tempered, or what do I do?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.10,1:39:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I lose patience.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.90,1:39:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Lose patience, you lose patience.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:17.24,1:39:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:17.88,1:39:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go on to the next.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:21.27,1:39:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The, we said that the mind has us all hypnotized.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.10,1:39:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That actually 99% of the mind is silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:29.20,1:39:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a great example.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:29.54,1:39:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a really good thing to know.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.80,1:39:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Because people go into despair.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.82,1:39:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They go to meditate,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:34.86,1:39:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and the mind just will not stop like a TV set with no off switch.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:39.95,1:39:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's because they're looking at the wrong place.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.93,1:39:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They're looking at the content of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:44.97,1:39:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And what we need to look at is the field out of which
Dialogue: 0,1:39:48.73,1:39:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,thinkingness arises.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:52.10,1:39:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, 99% of your mind is silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:56.13,1:39:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,99% of your mind is silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:59.36,1:39:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:00.56,1:40:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we have permission to ask?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.58,1:40:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,99% of their mind is silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:04.34,1:40:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,99% of your mind is silent, but what are you complaining about?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:15.82,1:40:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The ocean is still and silent all the way down, and the waves are only on the surface.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:22.01,1:40:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:22.91,1:40:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to still the whole ocean.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:24.81,1:40:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you only have to watch the waves.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:27.57,1:40:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:27.87,1:40:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So the place to focus in both meditation and contemplation is to identify with the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:37.59,1:40:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,As I'm speaking right now, I'm talking about the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:38.88,1:40:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm speaking right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:41.02,1:40:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There's absolute silence below the field that speaking.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:44.34,1:40:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The speaking is not myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:47.83,1:40:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The speaking this is a surface phenomenon.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:51.95,1:40:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The self really has nothing to say right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:54.33,1:40:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's absolutely silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:56.84,1:40:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what's there to say?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:00.40,1:41:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to say, except to be with all that is as is as it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:05.52,1:41:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,To be with requires no commentary.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:08.60,1:41:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can see the egotism.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:09.96,1:41:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,vanity of the mind, that it always has to add to or make commentary on what's
Dialogue: 0,1:41:16.08,1:41:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,going on. If you ask the mind, you know, to stop making commentary, I'm frankly not
Dialogue: 0,1:41:21.16,1:41:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,interested in your mind, in your viewpoints. Oh, not interested in your view, my
Dialogue: 0,1:41:27.80,1:41:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,viewpoints? But aren't you supposed to stand up for yourself? Look at all the
Dialogue: 0,1:41:32.63,1:41:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,stuff in the society that encourages the vanity of egotism, you know. You're
Dialogue: 0,1:41:38.50,1:41:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,supposed to do this, you're supposed to do that, and all kinds of rights and stuff
Dialogue: 0,1:41:43.52,1:41:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,come up, you know, but it isn't my right to. It's your right to think, but keep it to
Dialogue: 0,1:41:47.84,1:42:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself. All right, so the mind is seductive. It appeals to the narcissistic
Dialogue: 0,1:42:01.27,1:42:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,core of the ego. There's nobody your mind likes to listen to better than yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:08.35,1:42:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It loves talking to yourself, listening to yourself, all your complaints, your
Dialogue: 0,1:42:14.70,1:42:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,wonderful ideas.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.42,1:42:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You catch the mind, you're supposed to do this, you're supposed to do that, all kinds of
Dialogue: 0,1:42:18.08,1:42:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,vanity of it, and you catch the seduction of the mind. So the narcissistic ego is
Dialogue: 0,1:42:23.18,1:42:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,vested in mentalizing everything and emotionalizing about it, whereas in fact
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.75,1:42:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,there's nothing there. Underneath all that talking is, there's infinite silence.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:34.93,1:42:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There's actually nothing happening, nothing happening. Why? Because it's
Dialogue: 0,1:42:40.36,1:42:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,outside of time, and it's nonlinear, so how can anything be happening in a
Dialogue: 0,1:42:44.54,1:42:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,nonlinear infinite dimension? The field of
Dialogue: 0,1:42:48.14,1:43:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness itself then is a potentiality, even in divinity. Prior to
Dialogue: 0,1:43:00.02,1:43:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,God is the Godhead. The Godhead is the infinite potential out of which divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:43:06.08,1:43:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and godness arises. The infinite silence, which is not busy creating or doing
Dialogue: 0,1:43:12.98,1:43:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,anything, it's an infinite potential out of which arises divinity, out of which
Dialogue: 0,1:43:18.74,1:43:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,arises all of creation, is the light of God,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:22.83,1:43:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is the radiance of consciousness, and as consciousness encounters matter, it
Dialogue: 0,1:43:27.47,1:43:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,springs forth organicity, which emerges as life. But it all radiates out of the
Dialogue: 0,1:43:34.53,1:43:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite silence that we call the Godhead. Yeah? Let's see if that's correct. That is
Dialogue: 0,1:43:45.17,1:43:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,correct. The Godhead is infinite silence, and it's just infinite silence. Infinite potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:53.26,1:43:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Infinite potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:54.26,1:43:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:55.80,1:44:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. And where did that arise from? And this is the hard part. It always was.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:07.04,1:44:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The hardest thing for religion to get is that divinity always was. There is no first cause,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:13.88,1:44:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's not linear. That which is forever has no beginning or ending. Therefore, it's
Dialogue: 0,1:44:19.52,1:44:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond causality. Needs no explanation. Yeah? Yeah. I saw that back in theology.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:27.24,1:44:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesuit University, playing Bob. First cause, Thomas Aquinas and all. That which is infinite
Dialogue: 0,1:44:35.82,1:44:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't have any cause. It would have to have a beginning and an end. It would therefore
Dialogue: 0,1:44:39.42,1:44:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,have to be finite. How could that which is infinite be finite? It's beyond cause. Cause
Dialogue: 0,1:44:46.02,1:44:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is a mentalization that you project onto the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:49.96,1:44:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So this is how the mind keeps itself busy, keeps you fascinated and entrapped,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:56.62,1:44:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,entrapped.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:57.62,1:45:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So in one hand, you have fun out of it. On the other hand, you're its victim. Okay, let
Dialogue: 0,1:45:03.96,1:45:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it go. So when you don't want to be victim of the mind anymore, you have to be willing
Dialogue: 0,1:45:10.76,1:45:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to give those things up.
